360,547
Implemented the next meaningful slice of the refactor and made the branch buildable again.

`SyncNode` now talks to the real server transport instead of a test-only shape: it uses the server’s Socket.IO path/auth contract, creates sessions against the server’s accepted request shape, stops sessions through a matching route, and patches messages via stable `localId`s instead of appending duplicates. The server now accepts both legacy and `SyncNode` session creation payloads, exposes `POST /v1/sessions/:id/stop`, and updates existing `/v3/.../messages` rows in place when the same `localId` is resent. See [sync-node.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.ts#L157), [sessionRoutes.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-server/sources/app/api/routes/sessionRoutes.ts#L239), and [v3SessionRoutes.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-server/sources/app/api/routes/v3SessionRoutes.ts#L102).

I also turned Level 1 into a real runnable test instead of an env-gated placeholder: [sync-node.integration.test.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.integration.test.ts#L1) now boots a standalone `happy-server` on a temporary PGlite DB and mints a token through `/v1/auth` automatically. On the app side, the branch had deleted the v3 converter before the app store/UI migration was done, which broke typechecking; I restored that path as an explicit temporary shim in [v3Converter.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/sync/v3Converter.ts#L1) and re-added focused coverage in [v3Converter.test.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/sync/v3Converter.test.ts#L1).

Verified:
- `yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync test`
- `yarn workspace happy-server build`
- `yarn workspace happy-app typecheck`
- `yarn workspace happy-coder build`

Remaining gaps against the plan are still substantial: Level 2/3 are not done, the app is still not rendering `MessageWithParts` directly, and `happy-agent` has not been absorbed/deleted yet. The branch is now in a materially better state, but the full spec is not complete.
